    "comment": "Rationale: The splice variant CAPS2b can fully rescue deficits in synaptic transmission (evoked release, readiliy-releasable pool) in isolated, autaptic CAPS-1/2 double KO neurons.\n\nMoreover, the data indicates that the priming function of CAPS2 lies in the N-terminal part of the protein (Splice variant CAPS2e, lacking the C-terminal MUN domain) can still (at least partially) rescue deficits in the readily-releasable pool size.. Experimental description: We cloned the mouse cDNAs of all CAPS2 splice variants as IRES-eGFP constructs into a Semliki Forest virus vector (pSFV1)...\nCAPS1/CAPS2-deficient (DKO) mice (Jockusch et al., 2007) from days e18 and e19...",
